trans-unit.source: Indicates which <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref> a property is related to.
For more information about using attributes, see [Attributes](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md).
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.RelatedImageListAttribute"></xref> class.
The `relatedImageList` parameter can refer to a property of the current object, or a property of a property of the current object.

For example, if you have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem> object with a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem.ListView%2A> property set to a containing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView> object, and the containing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView> object has an <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.SmallImageList%2A> property, you could pass `"ListView.SmallImageList"` as the `relatedImageList` value.
The name of the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref> the property relates to.
Gets the name of the related <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.ImageList"></xref>
The RelatedImageList property can refer to a property of the current object, or a property of a property of the current object.

For example, if you have a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem> object with a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem.ListView%2A> property set to a containing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView> object, and the containing <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView> object has an <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.SmallImageList%2A> property, the RelatedImageList property would be set to `"ListView.SmallImageList"`.
